# Space + Structure Thinking

Common misconceptions:

students may believe:

```text id="p2g1qe"
area
=
perimeter
```

or:

```text id="u7g6qe"
surface area
=
volume
```

Some may:

```text id="c4g8qe"
ignore
units
```

without understanding:

```text id="k9g5qe"
different measures
describe
different properties
```

Students may also think:

```text id="n1g7qe"
larger perimeter
means
larger area
```

instead of recognizing:

```text id="t6g3qe"
shape
and
dimensions
matter
```

Example:

rectangle:

```text id="q5g2qe"
4 by 3
```

students may answer:

```text id="v8g6qe"
7
```

for area because:

```text id="a7g8qe"
4 + 3
```

instead of:

```text id="g2g4rx"
12 square units
```

because:

```text id="v1g8rt"
area
measures
inside space
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="j4g6qe"
measurement reasoning
```

